<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link><description>World News Today: Read the latest world news headlines, Current International breaking news world wide. In depth analysis and top news headlines world wide.</description><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>2026-05-15T03:36:52+05:30</lastBuildDate><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" rel="self" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/296589292.cms"/><copyright>Copyright:(C) Fri, 15 May 2026 03:36:52 IST Bennett Coleman &amp; Co. Ltd, http://in.indiatimes.com/policyterms/1554651.cms</copyright><docs>http://syndication.indiatimes.com/</docs><image><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><url>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/507610.cms</url><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link></image><item><title><![CDATA[5 massive pyramids still standing today: Why the largest one is not in Egypt]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131084431.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Ancient pyramids are often associated with Egypt. However, the largest pyramid ever built is in Mexico. The Great Pyramid of Cholula, known as Tlachihualtepetl, is a man-made mountain. It has a massive footprint, dwarfing the Great Pyramid of Giza in volume. This Mexican marvel is often overlooked, mistaken for a natural hill.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/5-massive-pyramids-still-standing-today-why-the-largest-one-is-not-in-egypt/articleshow/131084431.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/5-massive-pyramids-still-standing-today-why-the-largest-one-is-not-in-egypt/articleshow/131084431.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-15T02:15:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131090712,imgsize-1952613.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Brazilian influencer on the run after fleeing sentencing in fatal road crash case]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131103034.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Brazilian influencer, Rosa Iberê Tavares Dantas, has become a fugitive after fleeing the country before beginning a three-year prison sentence for negligent homicide. She was convicted in a fatal road accident that killed a 31-year-old personal trainer. Authorities have placed her on Brazil's arrest warrant system and notified international agencies.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/brazilian-influencer-on-the-run-after-fleeing-sentencing-in-fatal-road-crash-case/articleshow/131103034.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/brazilian-influencer-on-the-run-after-fleeing-sentencing-in-fatal-road-crash-case/articleshow/131103034.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-15T02:35:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131103037,imgsize-994508.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why a Bill Gates-backed insect factory releases 30 million mosquitoes every week]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131103011.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/why-a-bill-gates-backed-insect-factory-releases-30-million-mosquitoes-every-week/articleshow/131103011.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/why-a-bill-gates-backed-insect-factory-releases-30-million-mosquitoes-every-week/articleshow/131103011.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-15T02:35:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131103021,imgsize-1598759.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[“He’s texting some hot actress”: Candace Owens reacts after Brigitte Macron slap claims shock France again]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131103036.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Candace Owens reacted after a new book claimed Brigitte Macron slapped Emmanuel Macron over alleged messages to actress Golshifteh Farahani. The French first lady has denied the claims, while Farahani also rejected relationship rumors. The controversy comes as Owens continues fighting a defamation lawsuit filed by the French first couple over her past comments and online series.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/hes-texting-some-hot-actress-candace-owens-reacts-after-brigitte-macron-slap-claims-shock-france-again/articleshow/131103036.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/hes-texting-some-hot-actress-candace-owens-reacts-after-brigitte-macron-slap-claims-shock-france-again/articleshow/131103036.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-15T02:34:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sehjal Gupta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131103030,imgsize-1960069.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Yale medical school discriminated against Asian and White applicants, claims Trump administration]]